name: death stage
description: End of the life of an organism.

name: death
description: A permanent cessation of all vital functions: the end of life; can be applied to a whole organism or to a part of an organism.

name: death AE
description: a serious adverse event that has an outcome of death.

name: sudden infant death syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by the sudden death of an infant that is not predicted by medical history and remains unexplained after a thorough forensic autopsy and detailed death scene investigation.
synonyms: Sudden death of nonspecific cause in infancy

name: cell death
description: Any biological process that results in permanent cessation of all vital functions of a cell. A cell should be considered dead when any one of the following molecular or morphological criteria is met: (1) the cell has lost the integrity of its plasma membrane; (2) the cell, including its nucleus, has undergone complete fragmentation into discrete bodies (frequently referred to as apoptotic bodies); and/or (3) its corpse (or its fragments) have been engulfed by an adjacent cell in vivo.

name: Stillbirth
description: Death of the fetus in utero after at least 22 weeks of gestation.

name: bubonic plague
description: A plague that results_in infection located_in lymph node producing a bubo, which is an inflamed, necrotic, and hemorrhagic lymphoid tissue. The infection has_symptom enlarged, tender lymph nodes, has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills and has_symptom prostration.

name: Age of death
description: The age group when the cessation of life happens.

name: Sudden death
description: Rapid and unexpected death.

name: cell death AE
description: a metabolic disorder AE that has an outcome of cell death.

name: Neonatal death
description: Death within the first 28 days of life.

name: Prenatal death
description: Death of a fetus in the uterus.

name: brain death AE
description: a brain disorder AE that results in the complete and irreversible loss of brain function

name: fetal death AE
description: a death AE that has death in utero; failure of the product of conception to show evidence of respiration, heartbeat, or definite movement of a voluntary muscle after expulsion from the uterus, without possibility of resuscitation.

name: Death in infancy
description: Death within the first 24 months of life.

name: sudden death AE
description: a death AE that has an outcome of unexpected death, 1 to 24 hours after the onset of symptoms

name: death neonatal AE
description: a death AE that has cessation of life occurring during the first 28 days of life.

name: necrotic cell death
description: A type of cell death that is morphologically characterized by an increasingly translucent cytoplasm, swelling of organelles, minor ultrastructural modifications of the nucleus (specifically, dilatation of the nuclear membrane and condensation of chromatin into small, irregular, circumscribed patches) and increased cell volume (oncosis), culminating in the disruption of the plasma membrane and subsequent loss of intracellular contents. Necrotic cells do not fragment into discrete corpses as their apoptotic counterparts do. Moreover, their nuclei remain intact and can aggregate and accumulate in necrotic tissues.

name: Sudden cardiac death
description: The heart suddenly and unexpectedly stops beating resulting in death within a short time period (generally within 1 h of symptom onset).

name: Brugada syndrome
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by abnormal electrocardiogram (ECG) findings and an increased risk of sudden cardiac death.

name: Increased oocyte death
description: An increase in death of oocytes, the female germ cell (egg cell), which can be observed clinically in the setting of in vitro fertilization.

name: sudden infant death AE
description: a sudden death AE that occurs to an infant.

name: sudden cardiac death AE
description: This is an AE which is a sudden loss of blood flow resulting from the failure of the heart to pump effectively.

name: premature baby death AE
description: This is an AE which is the birth of a baby at fewer than 37 weeks gestational age, as opposed to full-term delivery at approximately 40 weeks but the baby is dead.

name: Death in childhood
description: Death in during childhood, defined here as between the ages of 2 and 10 years.

name: Death in adulthood
description: Cessation of life at the age of 16 years or later.

name: Death in middle age
description: Death between the age of 40 and 60 years.

name: Death in adolescence
description: Death during adolescence, the period between childhood and adulthood (roughly between the ages of 10 and 19 years).

name: Aborted sudden cardiac death
description: Cardiac arrest that would have led to rapid and unexpected death had an intervention not taken place to prevent it.

name: life-death temporal boundary
description: A life cycle temporal boundary that marks the end of the life cycle of the organism.

name: GRACILE syndrome
description: A mitochondrial disorder characterized by fetal growth restriction, aminoaciduria, cholestasis, iron overload, lactocidosis, and early death that has _material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in BCS1L on chromosome 2q35.
synonyms: growth retardation, amino aciduria, cholestasis, iron overload, lactic acidosis, and early death
Finnish lactic acidosis with hepatic hemosiderosis
growth delay-aminoaciduria-cholestasis-iron overload-lactic acidosis-early death syndrome

name: Avascular necrosis
description: A disease where there is cellular death (necrosis) of bone components due to interruption of the blood supply.
synonyms: Death of bone due to decreased blood supply

name: process that results in death
description: A process that results in death.

name: Death in late adulthood
description: Death at an age of at least 60 years.

name: sudden infant death syndrome AE
description: This is an AE which is the sudden unexplained death of a child of less than one year of age.

name: Death in early adulthood
description: Death between the age of 16 and 40 years.

name: Sudden unexpected death in epilepsy
description: Sudden unexpected death in epilepsy (SUDEP) is a sudden, unexpected, witnessed or unwitnessed, non-traumatic and non-drowning death, occurring in benign circumstances, in an individual with epilepsy, with or without evidence for a seizure and excluding documented status epilepticus, in which postmortem examination has not revealed a cause of death.

name: Gastrointestinal infarctions
synonyms: Death of digestive organ tissue due to poor blood supply

name: Gangrene
description: A serious and potentially life-threatening condition that arises when a considerable mass of body tissue dies (necrosis).
synonyms: Death of body tissue due to lack of blood flow or infection

name: eye infection AE
description: an infection AE where one or two eyes get infected by bacteria, fungi, or viruses.

name: gum infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the gums.

name: joint infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving a joint.

name: wound infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the wound.

name: tooth infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving a tooth.

name: kidney infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the kidney.

name: bladder infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the bladder.

name: ovarian infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the ovary.

name: infective myositis AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the skeletal muscles.

name: prostate infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the prostate gland.

name: pancreas infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the pancreas.

name: urethral infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the urethra.

name: abdominal infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the abdominal cavity.

name: cervicitis infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the uterine cervix.

name: lymph gland infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the lymph nodes.

name: herpes viral infection AE
description: a viral infection AE that is caused by a herpes virus. Note that there are 8 herpesvirus types.

name: encephalitis infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the brain tissue.

name: endocarditis infective AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the endocardial layer of the heart.

name: Recurrent viral infections
description: Increased susceptibility to viral infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of viral infection.

name: Recurrent fungal infections
description: Increased susceptibility to fungal infections, as manifested by multiple episodes of fungal infection.

name: salivary gland infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the salivary gland.

name: encephalomyelitis infection AE
description: an infection AE that has an infectious process involving the brain and spinal cord tissues.

name: Viral infection-induced rhabdomyolysis
description: Rhabdomyolysis induced by a viral infection.

name: Recurrent Burkholderia cepacia infections
description: Increased susceptibility to infections with Burkholderia cepacia, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infection with this agent.

name: vaccination
description: a process of administering substance in vivo that involves in adding a vaccine into a host (e.g., human) in vivo with the intent to invoke a protective or therapeutic adaptive immune response.

name: rapid vaccination
description: A vaccination process that is implemented fast.

name: age at vaccination
description: Age at vaccination is the age of an experiment animal at the time of vaccination.

name: primary vaccination
description: A vaccination process that occurs at the first time to a host organization in a specified period.

name: tertiary vaccination
description: tertiary vaccination is a vaccination that is performed at the third time in a row.

name: vaccination protocol
description: vaccination protocol is the protocol of a vaccination procedure.

name: vaccination coverage
description: A measure datum that measures the coverage of vaccination in a specific area during a specific time period.

name: vaccination frequency
description: Vaccination frequency is a qualitative term that represents how many times vaccination has occurred.

name: secondary vaccination
description: Secondary vaccination is a vaccination that is performed immediately after the primary or the first vaccination.

name: Post-vaccination polio
description: Infection with live attenuated polio vaccine following vaccination. This is an extreemely rare event that may indicate immunocompromise.

name: quaternary vaccination
description: quaternary vaccination is a vaccination that is performed at the fourth time in a row.

name: vaccination route datum
description: a measurement datum that represents a specific route (e.g., i.p.) used for vaccination. Different routes can be represented using discretized digitals. 0 = IP; 1 = PO; 2 = SC; 3 = IM; 4 = IN; 6 = IG; 7 = IV; 8 = ID.

name: vaccination site cyst AE
description: This is an AE which is a closed sac on the vaccination site, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue.

name: vaccination site pain AE
description: This is an AE which is a distressing feeling on the vaccination site often caused by intense or damaging stimuli.

name: vaccination site rash AE
description: This is an AE which is a change of the vaccination site skin which affects its color, appearance, or texture.

name: vaccination site scab AE
description: This is an AE which refers a hard coating on the vaccination site skin formed during the wound healing reconstruction phase.

name: vaccination site scar AE
description: This is an AE which is an area of fibrous tissue that replaces vaccination site skin after an injury.

name: Post-vaccination measles
description: Infection with the measles virus of the live-attenuated vaccine. This is an extremely rare event and may indicate immunocompromise in some cases.

name: Post-vaccination rubella
description: Infection with the rubella virus of the live-attenuated vaccine.

name: Triggered by vaccination
description: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by a vaccination.

name: vaccination site edema AE
description: This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in thevaccination site tissue.

name: vaccination site ulcer AE
description: This is an AE which is a discontinuity or break in avaccination site membrane that impedes normal function of the affected organ.

name: induced by vaccination of
description: an object property that specifies a process that is induced by vaccination of a vaccine

name: intramuscular vaccination
description: a vaccination that occurs in the intramuscular route.

name: vaccination site eczema AE
description: This is an AE which refers to a broad range of conditions that begin as spongiotic dermatitis and may progress to a lichenified stage on the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site eschar AE
description: This is an AE which is a slough or piece of dead tissue that is cast off from the surface of the vaccination site skin.

name: vaccination site injury AE
description: This is an AE which is damage to the vaccination site caused by an external force.

name: vaccination site macule AE
description: This is an AE which is a change in vaccination site surface color, without elevation or depression, so nonpalpable, well or ill-defined, variously sized, but generally considered less than either 5 or 10 mm in diameter at the widest point.

name: vaccination site nodule AE
description: This is an AE which refers a small aggregation of cells on the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site pallor AE
description: This is an AE which is a pale color of the vaccination site skin that can be caused by illness, emotional shock or stress, stimulant use, or anemia, and is the result of a reduced amount of oxyhaemoglobin and may also be visible as pallor of the conjunctivae of the eyes on physical examination.

name: vaccination site papule AE
description: This is an AE which is a small, well-defined bump in the vaccination site skin.

name: vaccination site plaque AE
description: This is an AE which refers a type of cutaneous vaccination site condition.

name: vaccination complication AE
description: This is an AE which is an unfavorable result of a disease, health condition, or treatment such after vaccination.

name: vaccination site abscess AE
description: This is an AE which is a collection of pus that has built up within the tissue of the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site atrophy AE
description: This is an AE which is the partial or complete wasting away of a part of the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site dryness AE
description: This is an AE which is a medical condition in which there is local or more generalized decrease in normal lubrication of the vaccination site skin or mucous membranes.

name: vaccination site pustule AE
description: This is an AE which is a small elevation of the vaccination site skin containing cloudy or purulent material (pus) usually consisting of necrotic inflammatory cells.

name: intraperitoneal vaccination
description: a vaccination process that occurs in the intraperitoneal route

name: vaccination site bruising AE
description: This is an AE which is a type of hematoma of vaccination site, the most common cause being capillaries damaged by trauma, causing localized bleeding that extravasates into the surrounding interstitial tissues.

name: vaccination site erythema AE
description: This is an AE which is redness of the vaccination site skin or mucous membranes, caused by hyperemia (increased blood flow) in superficial capillaries.

name: vaccination site hematoma AE
description: This is an AE which is a vaccination site bleeding outside of blood vessels, due to either disease or trauma including injury or surgery and may involve blood continuing to seep from broken capillaries.

name: vaccination site necrosis AE
description: This is an AE which is a form of cell injury on the vaccination site which results in the premature death of cells in living tissue by autolysis.

name: vaccination site pruritus AE
description: This is an AE which is a vaccination site sensation that causes the desire or reflex to scratch.

name: vaccination dose (unit: CFU)
description: a vaccination dose that is used with the unit of colony forming units (CFU).

name: vaccination site granuloma AE
description: This is an AE which is an aggregation of macrophages that forms in response to chronic inflammation on the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site infection AE
description: This is an AE which is the invasion of vaccination site tissues by disease-causing agents, their multiplication, and the reaction of host tissues to the infectious agents and the toxins they produce.

name: vaccination site urticaria AE
description: This is an AE which is a kind of vaccination site skin rash with red, raised, itchy bumps.

name: vaccination site cellulitis AE
description: This is an AE which is a bacterial infection involving the inner layers of the vaccination site skin.

name: vaccination site hemorrhage AE
description: This is an AE which is blood escaping from the circulatory system from damaged blood vessels on the vaccination site .

name: vaccination site induration AE
description: This is an AE which is dermal thickening causing the cutaneous vaccination site surface to feel thicker and firmer.

name: vaccination site irritation AE
description: This is an AE which is a vaccination site state of inflammation or painful reaction to allergy or cell-lining damage.

name: vaccination site joint pain AE
description: This is an AE which is a vaccination site symptom of injury, infection, illness (in particular arthritis), or an allergic reaction to medication.

name: vaccination site laceration AE
description: This is an AE which refers irregular tear-like wounds caused by some blunt trauma on the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site dermatitis AE
description: This is an AE which is inflammation of the vaccination site skin, typically characterized by itchiness, redness and a rash.

name: vaccination mouse strain datum
description: a measurement datum that represents a specific mouse strain used for vaccination. Different strains can be represented using discretized digitals. For example, 0 = BALB/c; 1 = CD1; 2 = mixed/outbred; 3 = C57BL/6; 4 = OF1; 5 = 129/Sv; 6 = Swiss albino.

name: vaccination site anaesthesia AE
description: This is an AE which is a vaccination site state of controlled, temporary loss of sensation or awareness that is induced for medical purposes.

name: vaccination site exfoliation AE
description: This is an AE which aims to remove dead skin from the vaccination site tissue.

name: vaccination site hypertrophy AE
description: This is an AE which is the increase in the volume of vaccination site tissue due to the enlargement of its component cells.

name: vaccination site dysaesthesia AE
description: This is an AE which defines as an unpleasant, abnormal sense of touch on the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site hypoesthesia AE
description: This is an AE which is a common side effect of vaccination site which manifests as a reduced sense of touch or sensation, or a partial loss of sensitivity to sensory stimuli.

name: vaccination site inflammation AE
description: This is an AE which is part of the complex biological response of vaccination site tissues to harmful stimuli, such as pathogens, damaged cells, or irritants, and is a protective response involving immune cells, blood vessels, and molecular mediators.

name: vaccination site nerve damage AE
description: This is an AE which is injury to vaccination site nervous tissue.

name: vaccination site paraesthesia AE
description: This is an AE which is an abnormal sensation of the vaccination site skin (tingling, pricking, chilling, burning, numbness) with no apparent physical cause.

name: vaccination site extravasation AE
description: This is an AE which is the leakage of a fluid out of its container into the surrounding area, especially blood or blood cells from vessels such as on the vaccination site .

name: animal age at vaccination in days
description: A measurement datum that represents the animal age (unit: day) at the time of vaccination.

name: vaccination site hypertrichosis AE
description: This is an AE which is an abnormal amount of hair growth over the vaccination site tissue.

name: vaccination site joint effusion AE
description: This is an AE which is the presence of increased intra-articular fluid on the vaccination site.

name: vaccination site joint erythema AE
description: This is an AE which is redness of the vaccination site joint skin or mucous membranes, caused by hyperemia (increased blood flow) in superficial capillaries.

name: vaccination site joint swelling AE
description: This is an AE which refers a transient abnormal enlargement of vaccination site joint not caused by a tumor.

name: vaccination site lymphadenopathy AE
description: This is an AE which is a disease of the lymph nodes on the vaccination site , in which they are abnormal in size or consistency.

name: vaccination site joint infection AE
description: This is an AE which is the invasion of a joint by an infectious agent resulting in joint inflammation on the vaccination site.

name: post vaccination autoinoculation AE
description: This is an AE which can refer to both beneficial medical procedures (e.g. vaccination) as well as non-beneficial or harmful natural processes (e.g. infection or disease).

name: vaccination site hypersensitivity AE
description: This is an AE which refers to undesirable reactions on the vaccination site produced by the normal immune system, including allergies and autoimmunity.

name: Infection following live vaccination
description: An infection resulting from live attenuated vaccines (LAV), that is, a vaccine prepared from living viruses or bacteria that have been weakened under laboratory conditions. LAV vaccines will replicate in a vaccinated individual and produce an immune response but usually cause mild or no disease. are derived from disease-causing pathogens.

name: Post-vaccination rotavirus infection
description: Infection with live attenuated rotavirus vaccine following vaccination.

name: vaccination-challenge interval in days
description: a measurement datum that represents a length of days as the interval between a vaccination and a challenge in a specific vaccine protection study.

name: vaccination site joint movement impairment AE
post vaccination challenge strain shedding AE
specification of vaccination-challenge interval
description: specification of time interval after vaccination for challenge is a plan specification that specifies the time interval after vacciation for challenge

name: host survival to pathogen challenge after vaccination
life-threatening reaction to previous influenza vaccination
